    "404": "404- This error is a web page that people land on after clicking on a link that no longer exists. They can take all kinds of shapes.",
    "429": "429- You receive the error message because the user sent too many requests in a period of time. It is a server that asks you to stop sending requests.",
    "500": "Error 500, with its Internal Server Error message, indicates an internal server error in the http communication protocol. The web server then encounters a difficulty in finding a web page, without being able to precisely identify the source of the problem."
